NCR Corp is very optimistic that it willpost record revenues and profits for 1987, Charles E. Exley Jr,chairman and president, said.    "Much of our considerable optimism about the future isbased on the strength of a continuing flow of new products,"Exley told a meeting of securities analysts. "Our currentposition is the strongest in modern NCR history withnew-generation offerings deliverable in every major categorythis year."    For 1986, NCR's earnings rose nine pct, to 3.42 dlrs ashare, on sales that increased 13 pct, to 4.9 billion dlrs.    During the balance of 1987, Exley said NCR will pay closeattention to increasing its penetration of major accounts,expanding its third-party distribution channels and continuingits introduction of new products.    "In 1986, new products introduced within the proceding 36months accounted for more than 65 pct of our major equipmentorder activity," he said.    "At the end of two months," he added," I can say we are offto a good start" for 1987. Reuter&#3;